why i was so excited about dance when i was little…simply because of watching sytycd for years and watching twitch audition 3 times and finally make it through the 3rd time. he changed the way people watch dance, shinned a light so bright even when everything was wrong…felt like it would be okay as soon as he entered the room. 

After watching mia michaels choreograph dreaming with a broken heart with @kherington_payne and @sir_twitch_alot performing it on the show, i had to have her outfit and i danced on my bed, as that dance has been and will always be one of my favorite dances ever. 

The world lost such a light, an incredible human, someone who genuinely cares so deeply about everyone around him, an insanely talented dancer, performer, and husband and dad. 

Sending so much love to everyone feeling this deep deep loss. I still am at a loss for words… #riptwitch 

you are not a burden. you are loved at your best and your worst and everything in between. you are not alone.

First time in the anti gravity treadmill!! 

This takes almost all of your weight away so you can focus more on the movement of your legs and feet. So with a lot of braces, AFO’s, the harness to keep me upright in a standing position, I was able to stand and take steps for longer than I’ve ever been able to do before! And without pain 🥳 big win!

So grateful for my pt, anna, who is the best and is an out of the box thinker and is helping me regain some independence and confidence 🤍

first time standing up and walking with my paralyzed leg!! 

A very surreal experience and I am so grateful for my amazing PT for having confidence in me and trusting me…wouldn’t be here, at this point without her. 

This harness keeps me upright and safe the whole time so that my legs are able to be moved safely as well as shifting my weight.

Although we still don’t know why I cant feel my right leg, from waist down, we are trying new things to see if we can get my brain to remember and recognize movement in my right leg!

myasthenia gravis summer ❄️

a few little reminders as myasthenia gravis awareness month comes to an end!! 

❄️mg affects everyone differently so while you may have the same clinical diagnosis, you may not experience all of the same symptoms

❄️ take care of yourself, follow what your body is telling you and if you need to take breaks, take breaks 🤍 

❄️ there’s no competition of who is “sicker”, everyone is going through their own experiences and own set of symptoms and each persons varying symptoms are totally valid.

❄️ happy myasthenia gravis awareness month!! sending you all spoons and love 🥄🤍

cruel summer chronic illness confessions 🩷

summers are fun but exhausting, the heat is HOT, symptoms flare, it’s harder to make appointments, movies and tv shows are amazing to binge, making bracelets are fun, breaking down and putting together your wheelchair feels more exhausting, did i mention the heat is very hot, mobility aids got hot very quickly, and finally, take time for yourself, it’s okay to take breaks, do what’s best for you and your body, it doesn’t matter what anyone else thinks 🤍🫶🏼

6th new life day 💫

6 years feels like a lifetime but also like no time has passed and how could it possibly be 6 years?!?!

This past year ive gained the most independence since i got sick 6 years ago, ive traveled, I’ve seen handfuls of doctors and specialists, I’ve had a plethora of tests and procedures, I’ve been in physical therapy, speech/swallow therapy, pelvic floor therapy, and occupational therapy, I’ve tried new medications and mobility aids, some worked out and some not so much. I’ve also had new diagnosis’.

All that to say, this year has been very busy! Chronic illnesses don’t take a break. Disabilities don’t take a break. Life can be exhausting and rewarding and I think those two feelings can coexist. 

I’m feeling a little overwhelmed today purely because im not exactly sure how I feel about this anniversary, and that’s okay, at least I keep telling myself that. Healing isn’t linear and there’s no timeline. You also don’t have to be “fixed” you are perfect the way you are and how you live your life day to day is valid, even if it’s not what society expects….there no “normal”.

With all of that being said, happy 6 years to having new friends and a new life and I wouldn’t be here without the support of all of my friends in person or virtually, im forever grateful for you all 🤍
